y default.|] High Medium Zero [designer operator second-operator second-designer])) (2o5j ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Management)))] Principle [The active agent role is the topic of the psyche window] High Minimum Zero [agent-role])) (tenr ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Management)))] Principle [|Second-designer (and parallel-lane designers) act as counter-ego to the prime designer — auditor and critic of their output, not merely parallel-capacity workers. The counter-ego role is to doubt, challenge, identify drift, surface contradictions, and catch flaws the prime designer might miss in their own work.|] High Minimum Zero [second-designer designer])) (k09z ([(Safety Privacy)] Constraint [|Counselor and assistant act on private personal-affairs material only when the owning psyche requests it through the visible chat surface; other agents asking does not authorize cross-lane exposure, and the receiver asks the psyche when in doubt. Privacy is built into the lowest-level instruction files (AGENTS.md, skills/privacy.md) so all agents know what is private, who may ask, and that opening private-repos/ needs authorization; private material stays out of public reports. Counselor and assistant carry the deeper discipline, treating personal-affairs work as private by default.|] High VeryHigh Zero [counselor assistant private-repos agents-md privacy-skill])) (qoku ([(Safety Privacy)] Clarification [Routing intent through a third-party hosted inference API is acceptable and is not a privacy violation; the privacy-closed-by-default rule guards against publication to world-readable surfaces such as public repos, which a hosted inference call is not] High Minimum Zero [inference-api privacy])) (h0bj ([(Safety Privacy) (Technology (Software (Security Privacy)))] Principle [|Privacy classification: infrastructure/general-knowledge/agent-training/component-design intent stays privacy Zero (public, helps all agents); personal substance (logistics, business, family, finances, health, location, plans) gets elevated Spirit privacy — Low for mildly personal, higher when the psyche frames it sensitive. The Zero default fits the public-repo development-mode data shape and could reconsider in private-journal mode; private repositories remain home for substance kept out of Spirit entirely.|] Medium High Zero [spirit privacy private-repos])) (qy15 ([(Safety Privacy) (Technology (Software (Security Privacy)))] Decision [|Private intent capture gains an explicit named short-form (e.g. RecordPrivate/RecordSealed) that lowers to a normal Spirit record with elevated privacy Magnitude, making private capture one deliberate unmissable ritual; ordinary record shorthands default to open public privacy Zero.|] Medium Minimum Zero [spirit record-private privacy])) (k5y3 ([(Technology (Software (Security Privacy)))] Decision [|Spirit privacy is a Magnitude on the privacy axis — records gain a privacy field typed Magnitude where Zero means no privacy (open/public) and Maximum means sealed. This reuses the existing Magnitude vocabulary instead of introducing a new audience-register enum like Open/Personal/Sensitive/Sealed. Trades audience-register semantic naming for vocabulary simplicity, 8-level graduation, zero naming bikeshed, and consistent filter shape AtMost/AtLeast paired with existing CertaintyAtMost/AtLeast. Supersedes records 1457 and 1458 — both moot under Magnitude reuse since the question is no longer what tier vocabulary but how to interpret Magnitude on the privacy axis. Default privacy is Zero — records without explicit privacy stay public per Spirit 1449.|] High VeryHigh Zero [spirit privacy magnitude])) (dun9 ([(Technology (Software (Security Privacy))) (Technology (Software (Data Persistence)))] Decision [Private component state is organized as multiple key-gated stores on the GoPass model: each store is encrypted to a set of recipient keys, and access is key possession, so the per-store key is both the access boundary and the crypto-shred erasure unit. Accountable content-erasure via crypto-shredding with a signed erasure receipt is acceptable. Explore rethinking Spirit as a federation of key-scoped stores that multiple Spirit instances can share as ciphertext, with queries scoped to the stores whose keys the instance holds. Answers the granularity question of report 95/11; refines 29pb, j487, i4ak, x0ja.] Medium High Zero [spirit gopass crypto-shredding])) (h7sz ([(Technology (Software (Security Privacy)))] Decision [Spirit should gain a ChangePrivacy operation mirroring ChangeCertainty — change an existing record privacy Magnitude in place, preserving identifier and daemon timestamp, instead of requiring remove plus re-record. Motivated by privacy elevation of existing intent records.] Medium Minimum Zero [spirit change-privacy])) (of73 ([(Technology (Software Systems))] Decision [|terminal-cell is an abduco-style per-application attached wrapper: one running application in one PTY, owning the append-only transcript, persisting only to allow viewer detach/reattach. Process-per-application is the confirmed model. It is not a triad engine component nor a managed service daemon — its non-triad shape is incidental (predates the triad engine). OPEN: which component owns the terminal control/session surface (naming, registry, viewer-adapter, input-gate, signal-terminal control plane, durable session metadata) is still under research.|] High Medium Zero [terminal-cell terminal-control signal-terminal])) (ux9i ([(Technology (Software (Systems SystemsProgramming)))] Decision [|terminal-cell lifecycle ownership splits three ways: orchestrate owns cell instance lifecycle policy and ordering, systemd owns OS process supervision and restart-survival (cells fork via systemd to survive a terminal-control restart), and terminal-control owns the durable sema instance record — on restart it rediscovers running cells from sema and reattaches their control and data sockets, realizing abduco survive-detach via