ad. *resource management*|] Medium Minimum Zero [nexus runtime-engine backpressure actor-system])) (ok16 ([(Technology (Software Systems)) (Technology (Software Operations))] Decision [|Research a way for core interactive programs (desktop shell/compositor, terminal emulator, launcher, dedicated rescue terminal) to keep higher effective CPU/IO/memory priority than bulk work so the user stays in control under resource pressure; survey Linux approaches rather than assuming a mechanism. Favor only the specific UI components needed over broadly restarting desktop session slices; the rescue terminal is separate so it gets protected policy without boosting heavy agent/build children.|] Medium Minimum Zero [desktop-shell rescue-terminal resource-priority])) (mlq0 ([(Technology (Software Observability))] Constraint [Spirit operations should report outcomes with self-describing NOTA enums and structs instead of long free-text status messages wherever the state can be represented as typed data. *error handling*] High Minimum Zero [spirit nota])) (tpvu ([(Technology (Software Observability))] Decision [|The CLI is the log surface: in testing mode the log socket routes back to the CLI, which displays all engine logs over the same wire substrate as production interaction — no separate logging daemon or sink. Testing-mode logging is configured by typed NOTA. Schema-emitted objects carry optional-compilable feature-gated logging hooks at the macro/emitter layer (off in production, on in testing) that log object usage through that same socket.|] Medium High Zero [cli logging nota testing-mode])) (32wj ([(Technology (Software Observability))] Principle [The categorisation of error kinds into subtypes develops over time, and that subtype development is one of the most important parts of designing the Criome stack. *error handling*] Medium Medium Zero [criome error-kinds])) (wgii ([(Technology (Software Observability))] Decision [|Once persona-mind ships, agent errors (mermaid syntax,